eds\n892: \n893: **Step 3: Verify import works**\n894: \n895: ```python\n896: python -c \"from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient; print('Import successful')\"\n897: ```\n898: \n899: Expected: \"Import successful\" printed\n900: \n901: **Step 4: Verify package metadata**\n902: \n903: ```bash\n904: pip show agentcube-sdk\n905: ```\n906: \n907: Expected: Package information displayed correctly\n908: \n909: **Step 5: Commit**\n910: \n911: ```bash\n912: git add pyproject.toml\n913: git commit -m \"build(ar-028): verify package builds and installs\"\n914: ```\n915: \n916: ---\n917: \n918: ### Task 12: Create integration tests with mock Router\n919: \n920: **Files:**\n921: - Create: `tests/integration/test_agent_runtime_integration.py`\n922: \n923: **Step 1: Write integration tests**\n924: \n925: ```python\n926: # tests/integration/test_agent_runtime_integration.py\n927: import pytest\n928: from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n929: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n930: \n931: \n932: @pytest.fixture\n933: def mock_router():\n934:     \"\"\"Create a mock Router service.\"\"\"\n935:     with patch(\"agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session\") as mock_create:\n936:         mock_session = MagicMock()\n937:         mock_create.return_value = mock_session\n938:         yield mock_session\n939: \n940: \n941: def test_end_to_end_invocation(mock_router):\n942:     \"\"\"Test end-to-end agent invocation workflow.\"\"\"\n943:     # Mock session bootstrap\n944:     mock_bootstrap_response = MagicMock()\n945:     mock_bootstrap_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"test-session-123\"}\n946:     mock_router.get.return_value = mock_bootstrap_response\n947: \n948:     # Mock invoke response\n949:     mock_invoke_response = MagicMock()\n950:     mock_invoke_response.json.return_value = {\n951:         \"result\": \"success\",\n952:         \"answer\": \"Paris is the capital of France\"\n953:     }\n954:     mock_router.post.return_value = mock_invoke_response\n955: \n956:     # Use client in context manager\n957:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n958:         agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n959:         namespace=\"default\",\n960:         router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n961:     ) as client:\n962:         result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is the capital of France?\"})\n963: \n964:         assert result[\"result\"] == \"success\"\n965:         assert \"Paris\" in result[\"answer\"]\n966: \n967:     # Verify session was closed\n968:     mock_router.close.assert_called_once()\n969: \n970: \n971: def test_session_reuse_across_invocations(mock_router):\n972:     \"\"\"Test session is reused across multiple invocations.\"\"\"\n973:     # Mock session bootstrap\n974:     mock_bootstrap_response = MagicMock()\n975:     mock_bootstrap_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"test-session-456\"}\n976:     mock_router.get.return_value = mock_bootstrap_response\n977: \n978:     # Mock invoke responses\n979:     mock_invoke_response = MagicMock()\n980:     mock_invoke_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n981:     mock_router.post.return_value = mock_invoke_response\n982: \n983:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n984:         agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n985:         router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n986:     ) as client:\n987:         # First invocation\n988:         result1 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"first\"})\n989:         assert result1[\"result\"] == \"ok\"\n990: \n991:         # Second invocation - should reuse same session\n992:         result2 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"second\"})\n993:         assert result2[\"result\"] == \"ok\"\n994: \n995:     # Verify bootstrap was called only once\n996:     mock_router.get.assert_called_once()\n997: \n998:     # Verify invoke was called twice\n999:     assert mock_router.post.call_count == 2\n1000: \n1001: \n1002: def test_multiple_invocations_with_different_timeouts(mock_router):\n1003:     \"\"\"Test multiple invocations with different timeouts.\"\"\"\n1004:     mock_bootstrap_response = MagicMock()\n1005:     mock_bootstrap_response.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"test-session-789\"}\n1006:     mock_router.get.return_value = mock_bootstrap_response\n1007: \n1008:     mock_invoke_response = MagicMock()\n1009:     mock_invoke_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"ok\"}\n1010:     mock_router.post.return_value = mock_invoke_response\n1011: \n1012:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n1013:         agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n1014:         router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n1015:     ) as client:\n1016:         # Short timeout invocation\n1017:         result1 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"quick\"}, timeout=30.0)\n1018:         assert result1[\"result\"] == \"ok\"\n1019: \n1020:         # Long timeout invocation\n1021:         result2 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"slow\"}, timeout=300.0)\n1022:         assert result2[\"result\"] == \"ok\"\n1023: \n1024:     # Verify timeouts were passed correctly\n1025:     first_call = mock_router.post.call_args_list[0]\n1026:     second_call = mock_router.post.call_args_list[1]\n1027: \n1028:     # First call should have (5.0, 30.0) timeout tuple\n1029:     assert first_call.kwargs[\"timeout\"] == (5.0, 30.0)\n1030: \n1031:     # Second call should have (5.0, 300.0) timeout tuple\n1032:     assert second_call.kwargs[\"timeout\"] == (5.0, 300.0)\n1033: ```\n1034: \n1035: **Step 2: Run integration tests**\n1036: \n1037: ```bash\n1038: python -m pytest tests/integration/ -v\n1039: ```\n1040: \n1041: Expected: All integration tests PASS\n1042: \n1043: **Step 3: Commit**\n1044: \n1045: ```bash\n1046: git add tests/integration/test_agent_runtime_integration.py\n1047: git commit -m \"test(ar-028): add integration tests with mock Router\"\n1048: ```\n1049: \n1050: ---\n1051: \n1052: ### Task 13: Create usage examples\n1053: \n1054: **Files:**\n1055: - Create: `examples/agent_runtime_basic.py`\n1056: - Create: `examples/agent_runtime_session_reuse.py`\n1057: - Create: `examples/agent_runtime_custom_timeout.py`\n1058: \n1059: **Step 1: Create basic usage example**\n1060: \n1061: ```python\n1062: # examples/agent_runtime_basic.py\n1063: \"\"\"Basic AgentRuntimeClient usage example.\"\"\"\n1064: \n1065: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n1066: \n1067: \n1068: def main():\n1069:     \"\"\"Demonstrate basic agent invocation.\"\"\"\n1070:     # Initialize client and use as context manager\n1071:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n1072:         agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n1073:         namespace=\"default\",\n1074:         router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n1075:     ) as client:\n1076:         # Invoke agent with a query\n1077:         result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is the capital of France?\"})\n1078: \n1079:         print(\"Agent response:\")\n1080:         print(result)\n1081: \n1082: \n1083: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n1084:     main()\n1085: ```\n1086: \n1087: **Step 2: Create session reuse example**\n1088: \n1089: ```python\n1090: # examples/agent_runtime_session_reuse.py\n1091: \"\"\"AgentRuntimeClient session reuse example.\"\"\"\n1092: \n1093: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n1094: \n1095: \n1096: def main():\n1097:     \"\"\"Demonstrate session reuse across multiple invocations.\"\"\"\n1098:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n1099:         agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n1100:         router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n1101:     ) as client:\n1102:         # Session is bootstrapped on first use\n1103:         result1 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is 2 + 2?\"})\n1104:         print(f\"Result 1: {result1}\")\n1105: \n1106:         # Same session is reused\n1107:         result2 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is 3 + 3?\"})\n1108:         print(f\"Result 2: {result2}\")\n1109: \n1110:         result3 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is 4 + 4?\"})\n1111:         print(f\"Result 3: {result3}\")\n1112: \n1113: \n1114: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n1115:     main()\n1116: ```\n1117: \n1118: **Step 3: Create custom timeout example**\n1119: \n1120: ```python\n1121: # examples/agent_runtime_custom_timeout.py\n1122: \"\"\"AgentRuntimeClient custom timeout example.\"\"\"\n1123: \n1124: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n1125: \n1126: \n1127: def main():\n1128:     \"\"\"Demonstrate custom timeout configuration.\"\"\"\n1129:     # Client with long default timeout\n1130:     with AgentRuntimeClient(\n1131:         agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n1132:         router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n1133:         timeout=300,  # 5 minutes\n1134:         connect_timeout=10.0  # 10 seconds\n1135:     ) as client:\n1136:         # Quick query with default timeout\n1137:         result1 = client.invoke({\"query\": \"Quick question\"})\n1138:         print(f\"Quick result: {result1}\")\n1139: \n1140:         # Long-running query with per-call timeout override\n1141:         result2 = client.invoke(\n1142:             {\"query\": \"Complex analysis\"},\n1143:             timeout=600  # 10 minutes\n1144:         )\n1145:         print(f\"Long result: {result2}\")\n1146: \n1147: \n1148: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n1149:     main()\n1150: ```\n1151: \n1152: **Step 4: Commit**\n1153: \n1154: ```bash\n1155: git add examples/agent_runtime_basic.py examples/agent_runtime_session_reuse.py examples/agent_runtime_custom_timeout.py\n1156: git commit -m \"docs(ar-028): add usage examples for AgentRuntimeClient\"\n1157: ```\n1158: \n1159: ---\n1160: \n1161: ### Task 14: Update documentation\n1162: \n1163: **Files:**\n1164: - Modify: `README.md`\n1165: - Create: `docs/agent_runtime_client.md`\n1166: \n1167: **Step 1: Create AgentRuntimeClient documentation**\n1168: \n1169: ```markdown\n1170: # AgentRuntimeClient Documentation\n1171: \n1172: The AgentRuntimeClient provides a high-level interface for invoking agent runtime workloads through the Router service.\n1173: \n1174: ## Installation\n1175: \n1176: ```bash\n1177: pip install agentcube-sdk\n1178: ```\n1179: \n1180: ## Quick Start\n1181: \n1182: ```python\n1183: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n1184: \n1185: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n1186:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n1187:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n1188: ) as client:\n1189:     result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is the capital of France?\"})\n1190:     print(result)\n1191: ```\n1192: \n1193: ## Configuration\n1194: \n1195: ### Environment Variables\n1196: \n1197: | Variable | Description | Required |\n1198: |----------|-------------|----------|\n1199: | `ROUTER_URL` | Router service URL | No (can be passed to constructor) |\n1200: \n1201: ### Constructor Parameters\n1202: \n1203: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n1204: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n1205: | `agent_name` | str | Required | Agent runtime name |\n1206: | `namespace` | str | \"default\" | Kubernetes namespace |\n1207: | `router_url` | str \\| None | None | Router URL |\n1208: | `verbose` | bool | False | Enable verbose logging |\n1209: | `session_id` | str \\| None | None | Existing session ID to reuse |\n1210: | `timeout` | int | 120 | Read timeout in seconds |\n1211: | `connect_timeout` | float | 5.0 | Connection timeout in seconds |\n1212: \n1213: ## API Reference\n1214: \n1215: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n1216: \n1217: #### `__init__(agent_name, namespace=\"default\", router_url=None, verbose=False, session_id=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n1218: \n1219: Initialize the AgentRuntimeClient.\n1220: \n1221: #### `__enter__()`\n1222: \n1223: Enter context manager. Returns `self`.\n1224: \n1225: #### `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`\n1226: \n1227: Exit context manager. Calls `close()`.\n1228: \n1229: #### `invoke(payload, timeout=None)`\n1230: \n1231: Invoke the agent runtime with a payload.\n1232: \n1233: **Parameters:**\n1234: - `payload`: Dict[str, Any] - JSON payload to send\n1235: - `timeout`: Optional[float] - Timeout in seconds (overrides default)\n1236: \n1237: **Returns:** Dict[str, Any] - Response JSON\n1238: \n1239: **Raises:**\n1240: - `ValueError`: If session_id is not initialized\n1241: - `requests.RequestException`: If the request fails\n1242: \n1243: #### `close()`\n1244: \n1245: Close the underlying HTTP session.\n1246: \n1247: ## Session Management\n1248: \n1249: ### Automatic Session Bootstrap\n1250: \n1251: When `session_id` is not provided, the client automatically bootstraps a session ID from the Router:\n1252: \n1253: ```python\n1254: client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n1255: # Session ID is bootstrapped on first use\n1256: result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"hello\"})\n1257: ```\n1258: \n1259: ### Session Reuse\n1260: \n1261: You can reuse an existing session by providing `session_id`:\n1262: \n1263: ```python\n1264: client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n1265:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n1266:     session_id=\"existing-session-id\"\n1267: )\n1268: # Skips bootstrap, uses provided session ID\n1269: result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"hello\"})\n1270: ```\n1271: \n1272: ## Error Handling\n1273: \n1274: ```python\n1275: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n1276: \n1277: try:\n1278:     with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\") as client:\n1279:         result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"test\"})\n1280: except ValueError as e:\n1281:     print(f\"Configuration error: {e}\")\n1282: except requests.RequestException as e:\n1283:     print(f\"Network error: {e}\")\n1284: ```\n1285: \n1286: ## Examples\n1287: \n1288: See the `examples/` directory for complete usage examples:\n1289: - `agent_runtime_basic.py` - Basic usage\n1290: - `agent_runtime_session_reuse.py` - Session reuse\n1291: - `agent_runtime_custom_timeout.py` - Custom timeout configuration\n1292: ```\n1293: \n1294: **Step 2: Update main README.md**\n1295: \n1296: Add section about AgentRuntimeClient to README.md.\n1297: \n1298: **Step 3: Commit**\n1299: \n1300: ```bash\n1301: git add README.md docs/agent_runtime_client.md\n1302: git commit -m \"docs(ar-028): update AgentRuntimeClient documentation\"\n1303: ```\n1304: \n1305: ---\n1306: \n1307: ### Task 15: Final verification and cleanup\n1308: \n1309: **Files:**\n1310: - None (verification task)\n1311: \n1312: **Step 1: Run all tests**\n1313: \n1314: ```bash\n1315: python -m pytest tests/ -v --cov=agentcube\n1316: ```\n1317: \n1318: Expected: All tests PASS with >80% coverage\n1319: \n1320: **Step 2: Run linting**\n1321: \n1322: ```bash\n1323: ruff check agentcube/\n1324: ```\n1325: \n1326: Fix any linting issues.\n1327: \n1328: **Step 3: Run type checking**\n1329: \n1330: ```bash\n1331: mypy agentcube/\n1332: ```\n1333: \n1334: Expected: No type errors\n1335: \n1336: **Step 4: Verify package builds**\n1337: \n1338: ```bash\n1339: python -m build\n1340: ```\n1341: \n1342: Expected: Build succeeds\n1343: \n1344: **Step 5: Verify all examples run (optional)**\n1345: \n1346: ```bash\n1347: python examples/agent_runtime_basic.py\n1348: python examples/agent_runtime_session_reuse.py\n1349: python examples/agent_runtime_custom_timeout.py\n1350: ```\n1351: \n1352: **Step 6: Update CHANGE.md**\n1353: \n1354: Add entry for AR-028 implementation.\n1355: \n1356: **Step 7: Final commit**\n1357: \n1358: ```bash\n1359: git add CHANGE.md\n1360: git commit -m \"chore(ar-028): final verification and cleanup\"\n1361: ```\n1362: \n1363: ---\n1364: \n1365: ## Summary\n1366: \n1367: This implementation plan breaks down AR-028 (SDK AgentRuntimeClient) into 15 atomic, independently verifiable tasks:\n1368: \n1369: 1. **Verify AgentRuntimeClient class structure** - Ensure all required methods and attributes exist\n1370: 2. **Verify AgentRuntimeClient initialization** - Test all constructor parameters and defaults\n1371: 3. **Verify context manager support** - Test `__enter__`/`__exit__` behavior\n1372: 4. **Verify invoke method** - Test invocation with various payloads and timeouts\n1373: 5. **Verify AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** - Test HTTP client implementation\n1374: 6. **Verify HTTP session utilities** - Test connection pooling and retry strategy\n1375: 7. **Verify logging utilities** - Test logger creation and configuration\n1376: 8. **Verify exception hierarchy** - Test all exception classes\n1377: 9. **Run all tests with coverage** - Ensure >80% code coverage\n1378: 10. **Verify type checking** - Run mypy and fix type errors\n1379: 11. **Verify package builds** - Ensure package builds and installs correctly\n1380: 12. **Create integration tests** - Test end-to-end workflows\n1381: 13. **Create usage examples** - Provide example code\n1382: 14. **Update documentation** - Create comprehensive docs\n1383: 15. **Final verification** - Run all checks and cleanup\n1384: \n1385: Each task follows the verification pattern:\n1386: - Write comprehensive tests\n1387: - Run tests to verify behavior\n1388: - Document findings\n1389: - Commit changes\n1390: \n1391: The implementation ensures:\n1392: - AgentRuntimeClient provides a simple, intuitive API\n1393: - Session management is automatic and seamless\n1394: - Context manager support ensures proper resource cleanup\n1395: - Error handling is clear and informative\n1396: - Connection pooling optimizes performance\n1397: - High test coverage and code quality\n1398: - Comprehensive documentation and examples\n\n(End of file - total 1398 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 Implementation Plan\n\n**Feature:** AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n**Goal:** Implement the AgentRuntimeClient in the AgentCube Python SDK, providing a streamlined interface for invoking agent runtime workloads through the Router service with proper session management.\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- AgentRuntimeClient provides high-level API for agent runtime interactions\n- Session ID is bootstrapped from Router or reused from existing session\n- Context manager support ensures proper resource cleanup\n- Invoke method handles HTTP communication via Router with proper timeout configuration\n- Connection pooling is implemented via requests.Session\n- Error handling includes session validation and HTTP error propagation\n- Unit tests achieve >80% code coverage\n- Integration tests work with real Router service\n**Architecture:** Python SDK client with AgentRuntimeClient (main API) and AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (HTTP layer), following context manager pattern for resource cleanup.\n**Tech Stack:** Python 3.10+, requests ^2.31.0\n**Frontend validation:** No\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Verify AgentRuntimeClient class structure","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775891802605,"end":1775891802630}}}}
